    "Dendritic spine pathology: The initial observation of dendritic spine loss occurred in hippocampal pyramidal neurons and dentate granule cells among individuals with TLE (Scheibel et al., 1974), providing a plausible mechanism to elucidate the learning and memory challenges experienced by these patients (Chen et al., 2010).",
